title: "A Society for All" souvenir cover design contest opens
content_text: A territory-wide design competition for a souvenir cover with the theme on "A Society for All" is organised to mark the conclusion of the Asian and Pacific Decade of Disabled Persons. The competition is jointly organised by the Health and Welfare Bureau (HWB), the Hongkong Post and the Rehabilitation Advisory Committee's Sub-Committee on Public Education on Rehabilitation. A spokesman for HWB said the United Nation's Economic and Social Commission of Asia and the Pacific had declared the period from 1993-2002 as the Asian and Pacific Decade of Disabled Persons. "The

Asian and Pacific Decade of Disabled Persons. "The
objective of the Decade is to promote equal opportunities and full
participation for people with disabilities in the Asia and Pacific region
so as to foster the integration of the disabled into the community,"
the spokesman said. "With
a theme on 'A Society for All', the competition will place special
emphasis on the achievements of disabled persons in various fields and
their contributions to society. "This
would help enhancing public understanding of the fact that given
appropriate training and opportunity, it is possible for people with

appropriate training and opportunity, it is possible for people with
disabilities to develop their potential and participate fully in the
community," he said. The
souvenir cover design competition is open to all residents of Hong Kong,
irrespective of age. A total of eight winning entries will be selected.
Winners will be awarded with certificates of merit and up to HK$5,000 in
cash prize.  Entry
forms are available at all post offices (except mobile post offices), Home
Affairs Department's District Offices and HWB's Rehabilitation Division on

Affairs Department's District Offices and HWB's Rehabilitation Division on 20th floor, Murray Building, 2 Garden Road, Central, Hong Kong. The forms can also be downloaded from HWB's web site at http://www.info.gov.hk/hwb . Entries must be sent by April 30, 2002 to the Hongkong Post Philatelic Bureau, 1st floor, Trade Square, 681 Cheung Sha Wan Road, Kowloon, either by mail or in person. Selection

in person. Selection
of winners will take place in May/June 2002.  Results of the
Competition will be announced on 15 July, 2002.
